I need to see the actual Alloy code in `reference.als` to help fix it. The error message you're showing is not an Alloy syntax or semantic error — it's a system-level error indicating that Java is not installed or not found on your machine.

Alloy requires Java to run. To fix this:

1. Install Java (JDK or JRE) from https://www.java.com or https://adoptium.net
2. Make sure `java` is on your system PATH

Since this is not a code error, there are no changes to make to the Alloy file. However, since you asked me to return only valid Alloy code, please provide the contents of `reference.als` and any actual Alloy-related error messages, and I'll be happy to fix them.